answersResultList.title: You sort of get body language, but not always.
answersResultList.resultContent: You're OK at picking up social cues, but stuff goes over your head, too. Look directly into people's eyes when you're talking. Tune into their nervous gestures. Also, hang out with animals for a while and watch how they are in the world. People are animals, too - we just don't have tails to wag or tuck between our legs!

answersResultList.title: You don't understand how to read body language.
answersResultList.resultContent: You really don't know what's going on, do you? Maybe you spend too much time in your head or home alone. Maybe you think words speak louder than actions and people always say what they mean. Maybe you're out of touch with your own body. Start working out or cuddling up with someone - and pay more attention to responses. That's where understanding body language begins.
